                                            A blast from the past: these vintage PC speakers will transport you back in time.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The further back you go into PC history, the less variety there is when it comes to peripherals. There are a few peripherals that were so common a great many of us used the same ones, or at least there were so many clones that we almost did!</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/remembering-the-iconic-pc-speakers-that-seemed-to-be-everywhere/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Steam's Latest Update Has More Library and Design Settings]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/steam-gives-you-more-control-over-your-game-library-and-ui/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/white-steam-logo-on-a-gray-background.jpg" length="58" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Steam]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You no longer need to sort your Steam library by alphabetical order.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>A new Steam app update has just been released that brings custom sorting for games, CPU temperature monitoring, and a bunch of new accessibility settings for desktop mode. It's rolling out now to Windows, Mac, and Linux.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 16:11:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/steam-gives-you-more-control-over-your-game-library-and-ui/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Pixel Watch 4 vs. Galaxy Watch 8: Which Is the Better Android Wearable for You?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/pixel-watch-4-vs-galaxy-watch-8-which-is-the-better-android-wearable-for-you/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shikhar Mehrotra]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/side-by-side-comparison-showing-the-pixel-watch-4-on-the-left-and-the-galaxy-watch-8-on-the-right.png" length="900" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel Watch]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Watch 8]]></category><category><![CDATA[Wear OS]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Google has finally caught up.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Pixel Watch 4 is shaping up to be a complete smartwatch and an excellent health monitor, but due to its pricing, it competes directly with the Samsung Galaxy Watch 8, another equally good wearable. So, which one should you choose? Let's find out.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/pixel-watch-4-vs-galaxy-watch-8-which-is-the-better-android-wearable-for-you/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Visual Studio 2026 Just Got Its First Preview Release]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/visual-studio-2026-just-got-its-first-preview-release/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/visual-studio-logo.jpg" length="192" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Microsoft's full-featured IDE has a new coat of paint, plus some AI stuff.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The first preview release of Visual Studio 2026 has arrived. As you might expect from a new Microsoft product, the big selling point is more AI integration, but there are some great performance improvements and visual tweaks as well for developers to enjoy.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 15:36:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/visual-studio-2026-just-got-its-first-preview-release/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Self-Hosting Isn’t Free: The Hidden Costs Nobody Talks About]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/self-hosting-isnt-free-the-hidden-costs-nobody-talks-about/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a7307819.jpg" length="1267" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Self Hosted]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><category><![CDATA[Homelab]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Old servers might be cheap to buy, but their costs definitely add up in other ways.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I love my homelab, but it actually cost me a lot more than I ever thought. No, I didn’t go on buying sprees and buy high-end servers with petabytes of storage. Self-hosting is great, and I love my homelab, but there are definitely hidden costs that I wish I would have known before diving in.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 15:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/self-hosting-isnt-free-the-hidden-costs-nobody-talks-about/</guid></item></channel>
